  "description": "Hugo Herman Lindquist (1869-03-11), a Swedish director known for his work at Rosteri AB Triangeln in Gothenburg. He was born in Alingsås to Ax. L. Lindquist, a factory owner, and Agnes Nyman. In 1893, he married Maggie Hill. They had four children: Margot (1894-1944), Elsa (1896), Lars (1901), and Hervor (1903). Hugo studied at Skara h. a. 1. and later pursued education in Gothenburg and abroad. In 1890, he co-founded Bröd. Lindquist with Carl L., and became the sole owner in 1898. In 1903, he co-founded the Association of Coffee Importers Rosteri AB Triangeln, where he served as the manager director until 1947. Hugo also held various positions in different organizations, including the chairmanship of the Association of Swedish Coffee Roasters and Rosengrens Kassaskåpsfabrik AB. He had a great interest in opera, theater, and music. Hugo was honored with several awards, including Knight of the Royal Order of Vasa, Commander of the Order of the North Star, and Knight of the Order of the Polar Star."
